Kim Jong Il Inspects Company of KPA Unit 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, August 4 (KCNA) -- Supreme Commander of the Korean People's Army Kim Jong Il, general secretary of the Workers' Party of Korea and chairman of the National Defence Commission of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea, inspected a company of KPA Unit 228.
 He was accompanied by KPA Generals Ri Myong Su, Hyon Chol Hae and Pak Jae Gyong. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He was saluted on the spot by the commanding officers of the unit and its company. 
 He learned about the company's performance of duty before watching its servicepersons in training. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He expressed satisfaction over the fact that the commanding officers and soldiers of the company are fully capable of undertaking any combat duty as a match-for-a hundred fighters. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He stressed the need to persistently keep up the work to thoroughly implement the WPK's policy of training. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Going round an educational room, a bedroom, a mess hall, a kitchen, a non-staple food store, a wash-cum-bath house, barns,  a power station and other places  of the company, he took warm care of the service and living of the soldiers. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He highly appreciated the achievements made by the company soldiers. He was greatly satisfied with the excellent living conditions provided by the company, seeing the barns swarming with domestic animals, fields under various kinds of vegetables and the barracks where electricity is in wide use. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The KPA soldiers are, indeed, pace-setters in self-reliance as they create everything from nothing, he said, adding that the appearance of the whole army is changing day by day and it has become a powerful engine for building a rich and powerful country, dynamically advancing the era and the revolution, as this staunch revolutionary spirit of the army is being given fuller play. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He called for concentrating sustained efforts on firmly building up the company, noting that it is very important to bolster the company, a main combat unit of the KPA.
 He gave a pair of binoculars and an automatic rifle to the servicepersons of the company as gifts and had a photo session with them.

Newspapers on Further Development of DPRK-Russia Relations 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, August 4 (KCNA) -- The publication of the DPRK-Russia Moscow Declaration signed by leader Kim Jong Il and President Vladimir Vladimirovich Putin four years ago was an epochal event of weighty significance in steadily developing the DPRK-Russia friendship on a new high stage in the new century, say newspapers Thursday.
 Recalling that Kim Jong Il stayed in Russia from July 26, 2001 and paid an official visit to it between Aug. 4 and 5 at the invitation of Putin, Rodong Sinmun says:
 Meetings and talks between Kim Jong Il and Putin marked a historic occasion in boosting the bilateral ties of friendship. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK-Russia Moscow Declaration adopted and published during Kim Jong Il's historic visit to Russia was a historic declaration that formally confirmed before the international community the will and stand of the two countries to develop the bilateral relations of friendship and cooperation in all fields in keeping with the common desire and interests of the two peoples and the requirements of the new century, ensure peace and security in Asia and other parts of the world and actively promote the common cause of humankind to build a just, new world. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The bilateral relations of friendship have dynamically developed on a new high stage for the past four years after the publication of the declaration. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Today the Russian people are striving to achieve social stability and national unity and defend the security and interests of the country under the leadership of Putin. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean people highly estimate the efforts exerted by the Russian government and people for social stability and progress, national security and interests and the building of a strong state and wholeheartedly hope that everything would go well in Russia. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is the invariable will and stand of the DPRK government and people to steadily boost the DPRK-Russia friendship with a long history and tradition. The strengthening of bilateral friendship fully conforms with the desire and interests of the two peoples and it is beneficial to ensuring peace and security in Asia and the rest of the world and achieving global independence and multi-polarization. The Korean people are convinced that the traditional DPRK-Russia friendly and cooperative relations that have developed century after century will as ever grow stronger in the spirit of the declaration.

Anniversary of Kim Jong Il's Work Observed 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, August 4 (KCNA) -- Rodong Sinmun Thursday dedicates an article to the 8th anniversary of the publication of the famous work of leader Kim Jong Il "Let Us Carry Out the Great Leader Kim Il Sung's Instructions for National Reunification."
 Kim Jong Il in his work systematically and comprehensively dealt with the undying feats performed by President Kim Il Sung for the cause of the country's reunification and independence and clearly indicated ways of carrying out the President's last instructions for national reunification. It is of great theoretical and practical significance that in his work he formulated the three charters for national reunification and clarified important and principled matters arising in accomplishing the cause of reunification and improving the north-south relations. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Noting that the work is an encyclopedic and important document which would serve as unshakable guidelines in firmly defending and successfully carrying forward the President's idea of national reunification and leadership exploits and achieving the country's reunification, the article goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The historic events and great successes achieved in the movement for national reconciliation, unity and reunification over the last 8 years eloquently prove the attraction and vitality of the work. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The historic Pyongyang summit and the publication of the June 15 joint declaration ushered in an era of independence and reunification and brought about a new phase and signal successes unprecedented in the efforts to warm up inter-Korean relations and the movement for national reunification. These are precious successes made in the course of the struggle to carry out the President's last instructions for national reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is the great exploit to be specially recorded in the history of national reunification that Kim Jong Il clearly indicated ways of carrying out the President's last instructions for national reunification and injected dynamism into the movement for the country's reunification with his energetic leadership. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 As taught by Kim Jong Il, the Koreans should regard the President's idea of national reunification and leadership exploits as the most priceless legacy and a solid foundation for accomplishing the cause of national reunification and firmly uphold and glorify them in order to carry out his last instructions for national reunification without fail.

Chongsong Bullojong
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, August 4 (KCNA) -- Chongsong Bullojong is a medicine manufactured by the Korea Pugang Pharmaceutic Company of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea.
 Won Hak Rim, 60, who lives in Pyongyang, had chronic gastritis cured after taking the medicine. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He said: I had long suffered from gastritis. Several days after I started taking the medicine, I felt hungry and had a cycle of diarrhea and constipation stopped. That wonder was that I regained strength in my feeble legs. People tell me that I have become younger. Now I dare say that Chongsong Bullojong is efficacious for digestive diseases and those of the aged. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It, strong in digestive ferment, is potent for preventing gastroenteritis, stomach ulcer, hepatitis, enteritis, colitis and other digestive diseases. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is good for detoxicating nicotinism, alcoholism and drug poisoning, preventing aging and various contagious diseases, treating arteriosclerosis, hypertension and heart disorders and recovering from weak constitution and malnutrition.
 It also promotes the growth of children. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Chongsong Bullojong is made with nutritive elements extracted from pollen and needles of pines growing in Mts. Kumgang and Myohyang. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It contains 40 sorts of microelements and more than 90 kinds of natural elements including essential amino acid, vitamins C, B1, B2, E, PP and K, protein, lignin, chlorophyll, essential oil, oligosaccharide and polysaccharide.

Heavy Rainfall in DPRK
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, August 4 (KCNA) -- A torrential rain fell in Pyongyang, South Phyongan, South and North Hwanghae Provinces.
 According to observations from 6 p.m. on August 3 to 6 a.m. on the 4th, Maengsan witnessed 142 mm of rainfall, Phyongsong 139 mm, Sariwon 138 mm, Pyongyang 134 mm, Songchon 96 mm, Pukchang 95 mm, Jangyon 92 mm and Hwangju 91 mm.
 In particular, for an hour from 3 a.m. on Thursday, there was as much rainfall as 66 mm in Pyongyang and 40 mm in Kangnam. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The heavy rain mainly hit cities situated along the River Taedong such as Pyongyang, Phyongsong and Sariwon. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The nimbus is slowly moving northward.
